The Chronicle Nqobile Tshili Police are hunting scores of individuals who were captured on camera in various fora allegedly committing acts of public violence in the last four years. Pictures of the wanted people have been released on social media platforms including on the police Twitter handle (@PoliceZimbabwe). <img class="alignnone wp-image-464770 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/wanted2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/wanted2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/wanted2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The government is clamping down on public violence as it moves to create an enabling environment for socio-economic prosperity, a key to achieving vision 2030. Anyone with information can contact their nearest police station or telephone numbers 0242703631, 0242748836. <img class="alignnone wp-image-464773 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/wanted3.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/wanted3.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/wanted3-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> More to follow. . .